Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> it's actually 200KB for one transaction fee now

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> that is the default max xtn size for KMD AC's which I helped come up with

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> 27KB is the old limit from Sprout days

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> @heguli97 in theory, we can support up to ~200KB files in one transaction, sent to one person, for one tx fee. For example, if you wanted to send it to 2 zaddrs, you would only have space to send a 100KB file in 1 transaction. The number of recipients effects max file size that will fit in one transaction

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <AkiraX> My email inbox gets pretty big. :)

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> on every full nodes hard drive

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> and yes, we have to come up with some reasonable max size file, or make the fees such that it can't be abused

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> and our blockchain does not grow to large in size

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> so a "fee market" may evolve at some point, if the Hush chain gets busy. We can also make more chains, or do various other things. They are good problems to have

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> You might pay more fees if you want your very important Hush memo to get to your biz partner right away, vs upload a large file that can wait until tomorrow @heguli97

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> the more fees you pay, the more likely miners will add it to a block, if blocks are full
